<user_id>108102445195917622529</user_id>< text>
I got a realistic wolf head with realistic roses tattooed by Robert a couple years ago. I walked into his old shop, not knowing anything but that I wanted a wolf. He said that he would draw something up for me. I came in about a week later and he had this beautiful tattoo drew up for me. I demanded we do it all in one session, even though he said I needed to do it in two. (Listen to him when he makes suggestions, lol.) 3 years later, my tattoo still looks amazing. It hasn't faded, it hasn't bled any. His line work is amazing, his work is amazing, everything about it is amazing. I definitely recommend coming to him for a tattoo. To this day, this is my favorite tattoo and the only one that I haven't regretted at least once. Also, he was very nice and professional but not stuck up during the process. I'm a talker during tattoos and he never once seemed annoyed. He answered any questions I had, before, during and after. I would give more then 5 stars if I could.< /text>

<user_name>Mariah Parker<//user_name><Gmap_id>0x80dcae0965579e81:0x3faee9b879986383< /Gmap_id><Review>Don't let the 4-star rating fool you into thinking Protech is a quality employment agency. I have had the worst experience with this company. I applied THREE months ago and still have not received any information regarding a job. They "place" you on to their otherwise non-existent waiting list. They will convince you they will call you when something comes up, but never do. I have only received two calls from them in three months. In the beginning, when they told me to apply in person. The second time, a woman called me and told me that I have a potential interview at this company and she will send me information. Never heard from her after that. I called a few days to see what was going on with the interview. After not being able to contact her for multiple days due to her unavailability, she said that the interview still wasn't approved and I had to wait. After waiting two weeks, I called again just for them to tell me that they did not approve and canceled the interview. They could have called and told me instead of letting me think I still have a job opportunity. When you call to get an update or information about a job, they will tell you they have nothing available, and "Try calling back in a couple of days." Or you have to call back later because the person you are trying to reach is not available. I have called over 30 times and each time is full of vague information, and empty promises of a potential job. Not to mention, when you are on the phone with them they try to rush the conversation and get you off the phone as soon as possible. It has been nothing but a hassle. Most likely the other reviews saying they got a job right away were for a warehouse. If that is what you are looking for, go ahead and apply. Just beware you'll never hear back from them unless you call continuously.  Apply to another agency (like Adecco) that cares about you and will keep in contact with you. Not one that makes you play phone tag by yourself. I am no longer wasting my time with this company. You shouldn't either.< /Review>< userid>

<rate>5<//rate>< Review>
Today, Aug 3rd, 2016, I needed a lid for my aluminum 12 qt. pot. I searched the internet, found some cheaper prices, but the shipping costs were double or triple the cost of the lid. No thank you... plus I didn't wanna wait for days to receive the lid. I needed it ASAP, now! I called ahead at Chef's Toys with my lid specifications; they searched their inventory within seconds, located it... living local, I went to their Torrance location to retrieve it. During my entire visit, the staff was extremely courteous and friendly (I liked that a lot)... one staff member at the checkout counter even had funny jokes-- about the spongy floor mat I happen to be standing on as I paid for my 12 qt. pot lid.

So happy that Chef's Toys could accommodate me, and immediately (rather than the wait associated with Amazon, et al.) I've purchased a hard-to-find item, previously (biscuit cutters). Today, per usual, was definitely a four-star experience for me!

Highly recommended for folks who're serious about their food prep tools.< /Review>

<Date>1466473613131<//Date><rating>5</rating><review>Being a landscaping novice who only needs to service one single family home, I realize I'm not the "ideal" customer for places like Bonnett who cater to contractors and professionals.  I've been to a couple other irrigation places in the area and never got the information needed to make sure I was getting the correct parts in the sizes I needed to effectively water my yard while conserving as much water as possible. I was a bit apprehensive when I pulled into Bonnett because it looked like the other contractor-centered irrigation places I'd been to. The staff here was EXTREMELY HELPFUL though! After visiting Bonnett I feel like I'll have the right parts even if I don't have a clue what I'm doing. Unlike other places the staff made suggestions and offered options rather than just selling me whatever I thought I needed. Bonnett is my new go-to for my landscaping needs, whatever those may be.< /review>< pics>
None< /pics>

<time>1501130784249<//time><Rating>2< /Rating>< Text>
Great Facility, nice fields and easy parking. However the  staff  have no concept of customer service and basic morals. As a group we have been playing here since it first opened when they were struggling to find teams to play on the fields. We grouped together and paid for an 8.30 time slot at our suggested rate which was agreed upon.  After a couple of months the office decided it was a prime slot and asked if we could move to 9.30. We agreed and gave up the 8.30 slot for 9.30pm. Not ideal but we are a flexible group. Cut a long story short the last two weeks they have cancelled our games and had the audacity to tell us another team wanted to play for an hour and half and has offered more money. can we play at 10.30pm to 11.30pm. the answer is no as we have jobs we have to get to the next day. Not only have we been pushed from our slot for money but the staff called and gave us 1 hours notice both weeks, i forgot to mention they cancelled our game two weeks in a row with no notice, well 1 hr, so I had to inform players that were already driving the game was cancelled. They should  also note that this is the wrong group of people to treat this way as many are valley team managers and heavily involved with valley football. I'm hoping for a response from the owner on treating long serving customers this way for a few extra $.< /Text>

<user>112339970460950335166<//user><name>gene henry ward< /name>< time>
1434824014517</time>
<rate>5<//rate>< Review>
I Love this place.
This US Storage Centers location is fantastic. I was curious about pricing and came in to see what this place was all about and ended up with the biggest unit they have. No pressure, no up-selling, just great, honest service with a smile. This particular location is just off the 110freeway and Carson St., so getting there is a breeze. Access is easy and the entire complex is quiet and CLEAN; the restroom is always spotless and smells great; the staff is also exemplary, they greet you, are generally concerned beyond just your storage visit that day, and are helpful beyond words. Additionally, if you are late on your rent, they will email you, call you and even send a couple texts to let you know so as to avoid a late fee after the 10th of the month. I was worried about the city and location of this place but this US Storage Center is no more unsafe than Fort Knox. Seriously. There are surveilance cameras everywhere and nothing goes unseen. Also, I actually forgot to lock my unit 3 times (the locking mechanism takes getting used to). The staff called to let me know each time after they discovered my unlocked unit; they do periodic walk-arounds to make sure each unit is locked and secure for extra safety. Wow! Not once has there been a crime issue there and that alone is calming.
So again, let me reiterate: I love this place, especially the staff; I was recently in a terrible bicycle accident and the staff is just so positive and concerned about my recovery as well. Says a lot. I always leave with a smile. Thanks US Storage Centers, for this great location and friendly, professional and courteous staff. Additional thanks to Sophie, you are awesome....<//Review>

<Rating>5</Rating><review>Our garage door spool was completely loose and kept ripping out of its socket, causing the garage door to open and close unevenly and to bend the tracks. My husband and I decided to get our garage door and motor completely replaced, since the garage door was most likely original to the house. We used Costco to get a good deal on garage install, and they partnered us up with ADS.

From the get go, ADS was incredibly responsive and helpful. We got a call the next day, and someone came out soon after that. The representative took the time to explain everything, break down costs, and show us different costs of different options. We were never pressured to go for the more expensive thing, just what he recommended for the most efficient garage door.

Jorge, who was our installer, did an amazing job. He took apart out entire garage setup, tracks and all, and installed the motor, the outdoor keypad, new opener, and garage door to perfection. He made sure once he completed everything that I was super satisfied with the job, and he even finished the entirety of the job himself in a span of three hours! <user>101999622991566536623<//user><review>By far the best McDonald's I've been to.  It's been a solid 10 years since I've had this kind of experience at McDonalds.  I think one of the largest contributions to my satisfaction was the fresh fries.  They were magnificently cooked to perfection.  Nice and crunchy on the outside with a hot potatoey inside that was to die for.  The salt to surface ratio of the fries were at a level few fry cooks can achieve.  People, these may have been the best fries cooked in mankind. I can now die a happy man after eating these fries.

As if perfect fries were not enough, my quarter pounder was elegantly made.  All ingredients were perfectly placed equal distant apart across the burger and bun.  There was no slippage between the upper and lower buns.  It is clear to me that whoever had made this quarter pounder had many decades of experience and possibly several years of professional development classes.

The setting of this McDonalds in the quaint town of Willits, CA added to the overall experience.  As the local watering hole for the town's people, you immediately feel like you have become part culture that makes this place something special.

Ba ba ba ba ba, I'm LOVIN IT!!!!</review><response>None< /response></record></dataset><record>

Good McDonald's. The food is always good but the drive thru is ALWAYS slooow. They rarely mess up your order but you have to remind them several times if you want condiments. I hate their new paper cups. The lids don't stay on. The ice melts in only a few minutes making the drink taste horrible. They should go back to their styrofoam cups or offer hard plastic reusable cups if they are wanting to be more environmentally friendly without ruining their soft drinks.</text>
